cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel framework for generating 3D objects using generative adversarial networks and volumetric convolutional networks. This work involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object recognition and generative modeling (cs.CV), as well as machine learning (LG) techniques such as adversarial training and unsupervised learning. The paper also deals with 3D graphics (GR) and artificial intelligence (AI) topics such as object generation and shape modeling. Finally, the use of neural networks (NE) is central to the proposed framework.
